'''Oil purification''' ([[Transformer oil|transformer]], turbine, industrial, etc.) removes oil contaminants in order to prolong oil service life.
==Contaminants of industrial oils==
'''Contaminants''' and '''various impurities''' get into industrial oils during storage and operation. The most common contaminants are <ref name="Hydraulic oil filtration">Hydraulic oil filtration.  A Publication of the Lubrication Engineers Technical Department. Number 62.</ref>:
* water;
* solid particles;
* gases;
* asphalt-resinous paraffin deposits;
* acids;
* oil sludge;
* organometallic compounds;
* unsaturated hydrocarbons;
* polyaromatic hydrocarbons;
* additive  remains;
* products of oil decomposition.
==Methods of oil purification==
'''Industrial oils''' are purified through sedimentation, filtration, centrifugation, vacuum treatment and adsorption purification <ref name="Study of Transformer Oil Purification">[http://www.internationaljournalssrg.org/IJEEE/2017/Volume4-Issue3/IJEEE-V4I3P105.pdf Shreya Salvi, A. P. Paranjape (March 2017). Study of Transformer Oil Purification. SSRG International Journal of Electrical and Electronics Engineering (SSRG-IJEEE). volume 4 Issue 3. pp. 20-23.]</ref><ref name=" Purification of transformer oil ">[https://www.researchgate.net/publication/309404071_PURIFICATION_OF_TRANSFORMER_OIL_in_PT_PJB_UP_PAITON Gusti Wahdaniyah, Purnomo Tri Prasetyo, Arif Setiabudi, Totok R. Biyanto (July 2016). Purification of transformer oil in PT. PJB. UP PAITON. International journal of engineering science. Number 5(7). pp. 91 -94.]</ref>.

[[  Sedimentation|  Sedimentation]] is precipitation of solid particles and water to the bottom of oil tanks under gravity. The main drawback of this process is its longevity <ref name="Waste Oil Recovery">[https://www.ijirset.com/upload/2016/november/62_26_COMPARSION.pdf Z.K. Bhushan, S.M. Anil, K. Sainand, H. Shivkumar (November 2016). Comparison between Different Methods of Waste Oil Recovery. International Journal of Innovative Research in Science, Engineering and Technology.Vol.5, Issue 11. pp. 20001-20009.]</ref>.

[[ Filtration| Filtration]] is a partial removal of solid particles through filter medium. Oil filtration systems generally use a multistage filtration with coarse and fine filters <ref name="Classic Ways of Used Oil Purification">[https://oilregeneration.globecore.com/classic-ways-of-used-oil-purification Classic Ways of Used Oil Purification.]</ref>.

[[Centrifugation|Centrifugation]] is separation of oil and water, or oil and solid particles by centrifugal forces.

Vacuum treatment degasses and dehydrates industrial oil. This method is well suited for removing dispersed and dissolved water, as well as dissolved gases <ref name="Vacuum Distillation Technique">[http://jnus.org/pdf/1/2017/1/1257.pdf M.M. Khudhair, T. M. Hameed, H.A. Alameer (June 2017). Using Vacuum Distillation Technique to Treat Waste Lubricating Oil and Evaluation its Efficiency by Chromatographic Methods. Journal of Al-Nahrain University. Volume 20(2). pp. 17-24.]</ref>.

[[Adsorption| Adsorption purification]], in contrast to the methods mentioned above, does not remove solid particles and gases, but it shows good results at removing water, oil sludge and aging products. This process uses adsorbents of natural or artificial origin:  bleaching clays, synthetic aluminosilicates, silica gels, zeolites, etc <ref name="Waste Lubricating Oil Treatment">[https://www.idc-online.com/technical_references/pdfs/chemical_engineering/Waste%20Lubricating.pdf N.M. Abdel-Jabbar, Essam A.H. Al Zubaidy, M. Mehrvar (2010). Waste Lubricating Oil Treatment by Adsorption Process Using Different Adsorbents. International Journal of Chemical and Biological Engineering. Volume 3. pp. 70-73.]</ref>.

==The difference between purification and regeneration of industrial oil==
Often the terms '''"oil purification"''' and '''"[[Oil regeneration|  oil regeneration]]"''' are used synonymously. Although in fact they are not the same. Oil purification cleans oil from contaminants. it can be used independently or as a part of oil regeneration. Oil regeneration also removes aging products (with the help of adsorbents) and stabilizes oil with additives. Regenerated oil is clean from carcinogenic products of oil aging and stabilized with the help of additives.

